 x + y = 41\\ 2x + 17 = y - 9 
y=\text{Your age, and }x=\text{Mine}
x+y=41\\ \text{And also }17+2x=y-9\\ \implies 2x-y=-26
\begin{pmatrix}1&1\\2&-1\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}x\\y\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}41\\-26\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}x\\y\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}\dfrac{1}{3}&\dfrac{1}{3}\\ \dfrac{2}{3}&-\dfrac{1}{3}\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}41\\-26\end{pmatrix}\\ \implies \begin{pmatrix}x\\y\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}5\\26\end{pmatrix}
